// --- Pruning: the cli-help probe and the doc sentence that DISAMBIGUATES it ---
{"id":"tart-clone-has-prune-limit-flag","kind":"cli-help","file":"specs/macos-ci/01-tart-core.md","argv":["tart","clone","--help"],"expect":"limit automatic pruning to n gigabytes","claim":"TRAP: `--prune-limit` is a `tart clone` flag (default 100) and it bounds HOW MUCH AUTOMATIC PRUNING RECLAIMS -- it is not a 100 GB cache cap. A flag in --help proves it parses, not what it means. The refutation of the 'cache cap' reading is tart-faq-prune-limit-bounds-what-is-reclaimed."}
{"id":"tart-faq-prune-limit-bounds-what-is-reclaimed","kind":"doc-contains","file":"specs/macos-ci/01-tart-core.md","site":"tart","page":"/faq/","expect":"limits this automatic pruning to 100 GB by default","claim":"The FAQ says `tart clone` limits automatic PRUNING to 100 GB 'to avoid removing too many cached items'. The 100 GB bounds what is DELETED, not the cache size. This is the refutation of the 'Default cap: 100 GB' reading, and the partner of tart-clone-has-prune-limit-flag."}
{"id":"tart-clone-has-concurrency-flag","kind":"cli-help","file":"specs/macos-ci/01-tart-core.md","argv":["tart","clone","--help"],"expect":"network concurrency to use when pulling a remote VM","claim":"`tart clone --concurrency` (default 4) is the flag the Packer builder's `pull_concurrency` forwards to; see packer-tart-pull-concurrency-passed-as-tart-concurrency."}
